    "intro_html": "<p>A gray house with a charcoal roof is the monochromatic choice in the cool register - refined, quiet, and broadly resale-safe. Charcoal granule variation gives the roof genuine texture and keeps the elevation from reading as one flat dark surface, the distinction between this pairing and a simpler gray-and-black combination.</p><p>Because siding and roof stay in the same color family, trim and door color carry the personality. Crisp white trim adds definition; a warm or bold door gives the eye a focal point. Traditional and transitional styles carry this combination most naturally.</p>",
